t not least, numerous publications on spiritualism. Photography plays a central role in his work and gives rise to a highly peculiar world of imagination. The photographs allow us to take a look at the world in around 1900 with all its oddities. For Conan Doyle’s contemporaries, Sherlock Holmes was a real figure. To Conan Doyle, photographs of elves, the dead and ghosts testified to their existence. This book collects these images, along with the imaginarium that surrounds them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLiterature and photographyxHistoryzGreat Britain. 0aLiterature and photographyzGreat BritainxHistory. 0aSpiritualismxHistoryzGreat Britain. 0aSpiritualismzGreat BritainxHistory. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aFilkins, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishz978311131918608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023z9783111318264oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831107976400 cprintz978139950218440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781399502207?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781399502207423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781399502207/original  a978-3-11-079764-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131918-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023